    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-12-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-12-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="364"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d364">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Dawson</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-12-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 20, 1905</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 199.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Continuing the subject of my No. 197, of the 15th
                        instant,<note n="a" xml:id="d364fna">Not printed.</note> political events in
                    this Republic, I have the honor to report that all has been quiet in this
                    capital since that date and no news of trouble in any part of the Republic has
                    reached me.</p>
                <p>The only points which give me any uneasiness are Puerto Plata and Monte
                    Christi.</p>
                <p>Vice-President Caceres left across country for La Vega, Santiago, and Puerto
                    Plata on the afternoon of the 18th. He goes to the latter place with the
                    intention of securing the adherence of the governor, Fermin Perez, to the
                    arrangement reached between the President and the Horacistas.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">T. C. Dawson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
